"'''Free Memory'''" is a comic story that appeared in ''[[Star Wars Tales 10]]'' and was collected in ''[[Star Wars Tales Volume 3]]'' and ''[[Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The New Republic Vol. 1]]''. The story was written by [[Brett Matthews]], art by [[Vatche Mavlian]], colors and letters by [[Michelle Madsen]] and edited by [[Scott Allie]].

==Plot summary==
After [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] fails to turn up for servicing, [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] finds him replaying the recording of [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia's]] message to [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Ben Kenobi]] on the [[CR90 corvette/Legends|CR90 corvette]] - [[Tantive IV/Legends|Tantive IV]]. When C-3PO asks why he still has this ancient history clogging up his memory, R2-D2 plays some other, as yet unseen, messages. They feature:
- a message from [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] for [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] and Leia just before he leaves [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] to its fate with the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]];
- a message from Leia for Luke just before the imminent Imperial attack on [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]];
- musings from Luke as he looks upon the [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]] celebrations at the fall of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]].
C-3PO decides that perhaps R2-D2 does not need service at this time.

